    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Bratislava Town Council (Prague, 26 August
                    1549)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>They will understand from the King’s letter what injustices and abuse
                            Sándor Rokawy’s wife has suffered from a Bratislava barber, and what
                            King Ferdinand I is planning to do in the matter. He is asking them to
                            do everything for Rokawy so that he can return to Eger and that Rokawy
                            and his family are left alone by this Bratislava barber.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Prudentes et Circumspecti Domini et Amici Honorandi, salutem et nostram
                    commendationem!</p>
                <p>Ex litteris regiae maiestatis ad vos datis intelligetis, quibus iniuriis et
                    contumeliis et verberibus uxor egregii <persName>Alexandri
                        Rakowy</persName>,<note type="critic">Sándor Rokawy.</note> aulici regiae
                    maiestatis a quodam barbitonsore concive vestro <persName>Urbano
                        Regio</persName><note type="critic">We do not know him more closely.</note>
                    vocato sit affecta, et quid sua maietas a Dominationibus Vestris propter tale
                    facinus fieri velit. Quare et nos easdem rogamus, diligenter velint suadente
                    communi iustitia ipsi Alexandro Rakowy de praefato barbitonsore citra dilationem
                    iustitiam et debitam exsecutionem facere, ut ipse Rakowy, ex quo aulicus et
                    contrascriba regiae maiestatis est,<note type="critic">He was Counter-signer <hi
                            rend="italic">(constrascriba)</hi> until 30 August, 1549, see Ep. 675.
                        Cap. 3.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15470818_1</ref>
                    <placeName>Agriam</placeName> ad servitia regiae maiestatis primo quoque tempore
                    redire possit. Deinde Dominationes Vestrae curent committere, ut ipse Alexander
                    Rakowy cum uxore et liberis suis in hospitio suo ab ipso barbitonsore et aliis
                    quietus permanere possit. Nam si deinceps quoque talibus iniuriis a quopiam
                    afficietur, regia maiestas non aequo animo feret, quandoquidem ipse est aulicus
                    suae maiestatis, credimus autem Dominationes Vestras nostra etiam maiori
                    amicitia id reponere volumus, easdem valere optamus.</p>
                <p>Datum <placeName>Pragae</placeName> 26. Augusti 1549.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Nicolaus Olahus episcopus Agriensis
                            cancellarius regiae maiestatis etc. manu propria</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Prudentibus ac circumspectis dominis, iudici ac iuratis civibus civitatis
                    Posoniensis dominis et amicis nobis honorandis.</p>
            </div>
